1
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:15,667
<i> Hazel!</i>

2
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,200
<i> She can't see you here.</i>

3
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,200
<i> What's your problem this time?</i>

4
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:19,700
<i> Call your lawyer!</i>

5
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,833
<i>Make him come here!
Let's face each other!</i>

6
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:23,333
<i>Why? Are you hiding
something inside?</i>

7
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:24,800
<i>Is that why you won't let me in?</i>

8
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:26,267
<i> Hold on! Hey! Andrea!</i>

9
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,133
<i>Who's the man
you were wih in the video?</i>

10
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:29,533
<i> Who is he?</i>

11
00:00:29,667 --> 00:00:32,133
<i>Why are you so desperate
to kick me out?</i>

12
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,633
<i> Why did you kill Joel?</i>

13
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,133
<i> You're so evil!</i>

14
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:37,167
<i> Andrea, stop!</i>

15
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,300
<i> Hey!</i>

16
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:43,200
<i>Why did you go
to Hazel's house?</i>

17
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:44,433
<i> And alone, at that?</i>

18
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:45,967
<i> I'm not scared of her, Mom.</i>

19
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:50,467
<i>Jeff said he's coming home
to be with Andrea.</i>

20
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:52,467
<i> Tell him not to, Coleen.</i>

21
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,867
<i> Joel won't come back anyway.</i>

22
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,933
<i> Colonel Sarabia has an update.</i>

23
00:00:56,067 --> 00:00:58,000
<i>They've officially ruled out
suicide.</i>

24
00:00:58,133 --> 00:00:59,400
<i> As they should!</i>

25
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:00,900
<i> Joel wasn't a drug addict.</i>

26
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:02,533
<i> Hazel killed him.</i>

27
00:01:02,667 --> 00:01:03,767
<i> You're a liar.</i>

28
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:05,867
<i> Sorry, but I feel guilty now.</i>

29
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,200
<i>You should already know me
by now.</i>

30
00:01:08,367 --> 00:01:09,967
<i> You know what I'm capable of.</i>

31
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:12,333
<i> No matter who it is.</i>

32
00:01:12,467 --> 00:01:14,000
<i> Hi, dear.</i>

33
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:17,533
<i>This is just between
you and me, okay?</i>

34
00:01:17,667 --> 00:01:21,433
<i> Your Dad Jojo and I killed...</i>

35
00:01:21,567 --> 00:01:23,800
<i> Andrea's man.</i>

36
00:01:23,933 --> 00:01:25,767
<i> We can't let...</i>

37
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:28,067
<i> our revenge fail.</i>

38
00:01:30,133 --> 00:01:31,933
<i> It was only you...</i>

39
00:01:32,067 --> 00:01:34,667
<i>my child.
I love you so much, dear.</i>

40
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,800
<i>Jojo, there's something
you need to know.</i>

41
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,000
<i> Hi, Alice.</i>

42
00:01:38,133 --> 00:01:40,100
<i>What are you and Jojo
talking about?</i>

43
00:01:43,733 --> 00:01:45,533
Andrea, no.

44
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:47,100
You think I'd leave you now?

45
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:50,367
You need someone by your side.

46
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:52,800
I'm okay, Jeff.

47
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:54,267
Stay there.

48
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,467
Spend time with Tetay and Daisy.

49
00:01:57,600 --> 00:02:00,133
You can't fool me. No.

50
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:02,667
I know you, Andeng.
I know you so well.

51
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:05,267
I know even the smell
of your fart.

52
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:07,867
I know when you're okay or not.

53
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,333
Andeng, I'm telling you.
You're not okay yet.

54
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:14,700
Let me be the older brother
that you need.

55
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,167
Yeah, I'm not okay.

56
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:23,067
Andrea, that's enough.
Hush now.

57
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,533
Don't let it all out just yet.

58
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:29,867
Wait for me. When I get there,
I'll cry with you.

59
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:33,667
I'll call you back later.

60
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,033
I just have to go somewhere.

61
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:37,733
Don't tell me
you're going back to Hazel?

62
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,867
Why not?

63
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,267
I hate that woman.

64
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,667
I'll get even with her.

65
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,033
Andeng, wait.

66
00:02:45,167 --> 00:02:47,467
Wait for me. I'll go with you.
Don't go alone.

67
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,467
No, Jeff.

68
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,533
- I can no longer wait for you.
- Sis, no!

69
00:02:51,967 --> 00:02:53,600
Dear...

70
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:57,833
Being tough won't fix
your problem.

71
00:02:58,567 --> 00:03:03,333
When you let
your bravery take over...

72
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:05,700
We understand your anger.

73
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,900
But...

74
00:03:09,033 --> 00:03:11,400
would Joel really want you...

75
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,733
letting your anger take over?

76
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,700
Joel's gone, Mom.

77
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:20,433
The person who taught me
how to be a good person

78
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,933
at all times
is no longer with us.

79
00:03:23,767 --> 00:03:25,633
The person who taught me
how to trust and love

80
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:28,433
is no longer with us.

81
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:32,733
The person I love is gone.

82
00:03:36,433 --> 00:03:37,800
Joel is gone.

83
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,567
For the longest time,

84
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:53,033
I couldn't trust any man.

85
00:03:55,767 --> 00:03:58,833
But when I met Joel,

86
00:03:58,967 --> 00:04:02,367
he made me feel like I could.

87
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:05,900
He showed me
I was capable of loving.

88
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:09,433
He took away all my fears.

89
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,100
He showed me...

90
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,633
I was also worthy
of being loved.

91
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,267
But now he's gone.

92
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:24,333
We no longer have a chance
to be happy with each other.

93
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,400
Because Hazel killed him.

94
00:04:32,267 --> 00:04:35,167
So I won't stop
until I avenge him.

95
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:37,033
Andrea. Sweetie.

96
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:41,800
Think carefully about
what you're about to do.

97
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:44,467
You might...

98
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,133
end up getting harmed.

99
00:04:47,267 --> 00:04:49,167
What if something happens
to you?

100
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,700
What will happen to us?

101
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:54,600
You need to fight,

102
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:58,300
however painful it is.

103
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:01,600
- Remember, we're always here.
- Sis.

104
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,833
- We'll support you, dear.
- Mom.

105
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:08,300
Andeng, I'll support
your revenge.

106
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:10,767
But wait for me.

107
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:13,700
I'll go with you.
I want to be there, too.

108
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:17,267
I'll make sure that Hazel pays
for what she did to our family.

109
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,800
Jeff, why don't you stay
there a little longer?

110
00:05:28,933 --> 00:05:30,700
Why don't you want me
to come home, Dad?

111
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:34,333
Your mom and I
are thinking of...

112
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,567
taking Andrea somewhere

113
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:39,167
to get her mind off
what happened to Joel.

114
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:46,667
We were thinking of sending her
to Australia for a vacation.

115
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,900
You're there.

116
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:51,300
She'll be with you.

117
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:56,967
You don't have
to come home sooner

118
00:05:57,100 --> 00:06:01,000
and leave Tetay and Daisy.

119
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:04,733
Daisy has already booked
my ticket, Mom, Dad.

120
00:06:04,867 --> 00:06:06,667
Well then,
when will you come home?

121
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,400
What time is your flight?

122
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:11,500
This Saturday.

123
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:13,867
I'll arrive at 1:00 P.M.

124
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,967
Let's talk about Andrea
when I get there.

125
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:20,433
It's better if all of us
are there for her.

126
00:06:20,567 --> 00:06:24,300
Okay, son. Your Uncle Able and I
will pick you up.

127
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,767
Okay, Dad.
Thank you.

128
00:06:27,567 --> 00:06:29,467
Let me make the most
of the day for now, Dad.

129
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,733
I'll take my family out.

130
00:06:31,867 --> 00:06:34,567
Okay, son.
Be safe, okay?

131
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,767
1:00 P.M.

132
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,800
Saturday, 1:00 P.M.

133
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,733
Do you already
know a place?

134
00:07:07,267 --> 00:07:08,133
Yes, Ma'am.

135
00:07:09,367 --> 00:07:10,533
Who's the target?

136
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,267
Oh, him.

137
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,200
This would be easy.

138
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:25,733
I just need a helper.

139
00:07:27,567 --> 00:07:29,733
I gave your number to them.

140
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,633
Sorry, bro.

141
00:08:02,767 --> 00:08:05,533
I took the wrong turn.
This parking lot is so far.

142
00:08:16,733 --> 00:08:19,067
He's still taking care
of his luggage anyway.

143
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,967
He's probably at the gate
when we get there.

144
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,133
Has his flight arrived on time?

145
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:28,267
He hasn't texted me yet.

146
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,567
Let's just go see him.
Come on.

147
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,100
Let's go.

148
00:08:56,033 --> 00:08:57,567
Hey! What's this?

149
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:58,933
Who are you?
I don't know you!

150
00:08:59,067 --> 00:09:00,267
Shut up!

151
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:02,433
Sir! Sir! That's my phone!

152
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:06,300
Dad! Dad! Uncle!

153
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:17,100
I don't have money!
Why are you taking me?

154
00:09:17,233 --> 00:09:19,167
Shut him up already!
So noisy!

155
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:20,167
You sound familiar.

156
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,000
Wait! Dad!

157
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,600
Help! Help!

158
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:34,233
Thank you, Sir.

159
00:09:40,667 --> 00:09:43,267
Bro, the plane
landed a while ago.

160
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,033
Apparently, it even came early.

161
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:46,567
Why is Jeffrey not here yet?

162
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:48,900
That's what they told me.

163
00:09:49,033 --> 00:09:50,400
Maybe something just went wrong.

164
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,967
Let's wait a little longer.

165
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:03,800
Are you sure, sir?

166
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:06,067
These are the flight details.

167
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:09,233
Yes, sir. The plane landed
almost an hour ago.

168
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,800
- An hour ago?
- Yes, sir.

169
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:14,200
This plane already landed
an hour ago?

170
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:15,600
Yes, sir.

171
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:29,367
Bro.

172
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:33,767
What do we do now?

173
00:11:03,433 --> 00:11:04,867
So he really didn't show up?

174
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:14,700
But Dad,

175
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:18,133
are you sure
the flight wasn't just delayed?

176
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:19,867
Andeng...

177
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,200
I've already asked
a lot of people.

178
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:23,267
Jeff's fellow passengers.

179
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,433
What if...

180
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:28,233
we try calling Daisy and Tetay?

181
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:29,800
Uncle...

182
00:11:29,933 --> 00:11:32,767
we don't have
their Australian numbers.

183
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:36,667
And didn't they only call Jeff
last Christmas?

184
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,633
We should've asked
for their numbers.

185
00:11:38,767 --> 00:11:40,500
Uncle...

186
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:41,567
I checked Friendsbook.

187
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:43,933
Daisy and Tetay's profiles
are active again.

188
00:11:45,933 --> 00:11:47,067
Jeff texted.

189
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,633
What did he say?

190
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:53,200
"Sorry, I couldn't make it home.

191
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:54,900
There was an emergency."

192
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:58,500
Wait, wait.
I'll call him.

193
00:12:04,133 --> 00:12:05,967
He rejected it.

194
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,767
Maybe he's busy?

195
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:09,767
Just reply by text.

196
00:12:17,433 --> 00:12:18,800
Let me go!

197
00:12:22,133 --> 00:12:23,467
Ouch!

198
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,200
Darn you!

199
00:12:36,567 --> 00:12:38,500
Who are you people?

200
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:39,767
Hurry, hurry!

201
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:42,633
Ouch! That hurts!

202
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:43,767
Let me go!

203
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:44,933
So noisy.

204
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:47,233
Help me!

205
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:51,767
Help!

206
00:12:55,633 --> 00:12:57,400
Don't waste your strength.
You'll just tire yourself out.

207
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:59,000
Help!

208
00:13:03,633 --> 00:13:05,000
Help!

209
00:13:05,133 --> 00:13:08,200
Help!

210
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:30,200
<i>Yes, Dad.
I'm just busy.</i>

211
00:13:30,333 --> 00:13:32,500
<i> That's why I couldn't answer.</i>

212
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:35,200
<i> I'll call you back.</i>

213
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:36,267
<i> Yes, Manuel.</i>

214
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:38,100
<i>You'll get to talk
to your eldest son</i>

215
00:13:38,233 --> 00:13:41,000
<i>once he's beaten
half to death...</i>

216
00:13:41,133 --> 00:13:43,833
<i> And begging to just kill him</i>

217
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:46,100
<i>instead of torturing him
any longer.</i>

218
00:13:46,233 --> 00:13:47,433
Get him up!

219
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:49,333
Get up!

220
00:13:49,467 --> 00:13:50,633
Stand up!

221
00:13:56,667 --> 00:13:57,600
Get up!

222
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:39,367
Thank you for giving me
his flight details.

223
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:43,633
Pretty satisfying to watch,
right?

224
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:48,133
One by one, they're getting
a taste of the abuse and pain

225
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:49,800
they put Jessica
through back then.

226
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,033
Where did you take him?

227
00:14:56,867 --> 00:14:58,200
Somewhere far away.

228
00:14:58,467 --> 00:14:59,867
A place where Manuel
won't be able to track.

229
00:15:01,933 --> 00:15:04,033
You want to come with me
when I go there?

230
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:07,700
Wait.

231
00:15:08,767 --> 00:15:10,500
Don't tell me...

232
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:13,867
you actually feel sorry for him?

233
00:15:15,367 --> 00:15:16,567
Hazel, promise me.

234
00:15:17,867 --> 00:15:19,533
This is as far as you'll go.

235
00:15:25,367 --> 00:15:26,567
Promise me.

236
00:15:28,633 --> 00:15:29,967
Fine.

237
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,267
I promise.

238
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:36,267
But if Jeffrey's body gives out,
that's not on me.

239
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:38,433
- Hazel.
- What?

240
00:15:38,567 --> 00:15:40,733
I can't control
Alonso's punches.

241
00:15:40,867 --> 00:15:42,500
What do you
expect me to do?

242
00:15:42,633 --> 00:15:45,867
This isn't the kind of revenge
I had in mind, Hazel.

243
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,600
I thought we were just
going to ruin Manuel's family.

244
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:54,167
Why are you suddenly
willing to kill them?

245
00:15:54,300 --> 00:15:55,500
That's not really
my intention.

246
00:15:57,400 --> 00:16:00,067
But if someone dies
along the way...

247
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,233
so be it.

248
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:03,533
Why?

249
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:06,100
You're getting cold feet now?

250
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,400
You are scared, aren't you?

251
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:14,300
But honestly,
why am I not surprised?

252
00:16:15,467 --> 00:16:18,200
You've always been afraid

253
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:21,267
of taking responsibility
for Jessica, haven't you?

254
00:16:42,233 --> 00:16:44,767
Felma and I already talked, bro.

255
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:46,033
We're pushing through
with the vacation

256
00:16:46,167 --> 00:16:47,767
even if Jeff isn't here yet.

257
00:16:50,033 --> 00:16:51,767
So we can rest.

258
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:53,733
And so Andrea
can grieve properly.

259
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:57,400
You wanna come with us?

260
00:16:57,533 --> 00:16:59,000
Of course.

261
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:00,167
By the way,

262
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:03,200
I've got partner hotels
in Singapore and Thailand.

263
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:04,667
Where do you wanna go?

264
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:08,400
Oh. Wait, it's Tetay.

265
00:17:09,767 --> 00:17:10,633
Tetay!

266
00:17:10,767 --> 00:17:13,767
Tetay, my princess!

267
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,400
Daisy.

268
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:17,100
Hello, Pretty Mama!

269
00:17:17,233 --> 00:17:19,333
Handsome Papa,
Good-looking Papa,

270
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:22,533
Aunt Andrea, Aunt Coleen,
and Didang, hello!

271
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,267
Tetay!

272
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,767
Where's Dad?

273
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:30,633
He's not here yet.

274
00:17:30,767 --> 00:17:33,333
He texted earlier.
Said he couldn't make it.

275
00:17:33,467 --> 00:17:34,967
He did make it, Auntie.

276
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:38,167
We even took him
to the airport.

277
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,033
Then where's Dad?

278
00:17:40,167 --> 00:17:43,267
Pretty Mama, please find him.

279
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,267
Sweetie, we'll take care of it,
okay?

280
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,967
Don't cry.

281
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:49,200
Daisy, we'll keep you updated,
okay?

282
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:50,633
Okay, Auntie.

283
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:52,633
Please update us right away.

284
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,067
So what now?

285
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,567
I know who did this.

286
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:03,067
It's Hazel. She had Jeff
kidnapped. I'm sure of it.

287
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:05,367
Andrea, let's not jump
to conclusions.

288
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:07,000
No, Uncle,

289
00:18:07,133 --> 00:18:09,233
think about it.

290
00:18:09,367 --> 00:18:11,300
She went after us one by one.

291
00:18:11,433 --> 00:18:12,600
First Coleen,

292
00:18:12,733 --> 00:18:13,600
then me.

293
00:18:13,733 --> 00:18:15,100
Now it's Jeff.

294
00:18:15,233 --> 00:18:18,167
There's no one else.
It's Hazel!

295
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:19,933
Why would Jeff suddenly
get kidnapped?

296
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:21,733
We're not billionaires.

297
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,133
No one's asking for ransom.

298
00:18:24,267 --> 00:18:26,433
We even got a text from him.

299
00:18:26,567 --> 00:18:28,067
Why would there be a text
like that?

300
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,467
This is personal.

301
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:31,733
It's Hazel.
She did this.

302
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:34,167
That demon really
hasn't changed at all!

303
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:35,167
Andrea!

304
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:37,000
- Andrea!
- Sis!

305
00:18:37,133 --> 00:18:38,333
Andrea!

306
00:18:38,467 --> 00:18:40,267
- Andrea, wait!
- Felma, we'll follow her.

307
00:18:57,767 --> 00:18:59,933
- Andrea!
- Sis!

308
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:05,967
- Sis!
- Andrea!

309
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:09,733
- Sis!
- Andrea!

310
00:19:09,867 --> 00:19:10,933
- Hello.
- Andrea!

311
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:12,833
Hazel!

312
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:15,033
What is it now?
You're disturbing my neighbors!

313
00:19:16,067 --> 00:19:17,867
What are you doing here
this time?

314
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,433
Breaking into my house
is your new hobby now, huh?

315
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:22,200
What's the script today?

316
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:23,400
And you even brought people
with you.

317
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:25,233
What is this, an all-star cast?
A family reunion?

318
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:26,233
So what now?

319
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,300
What are you accusing me
of this time

320
00:19:27,433 --> 00:19:29,267
- for Joel's death...
- Where's my brother?

321
00:19:29,867 --> 00:19:30,833
Where is he?

322
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:32,833
- What?
- Don't play dumb!

323
00:19:32,967 --> 00:19:34,967
- Where's my brother?
- What are you talking about?

324
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:36,600
Hey!

325
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:38,667
- Hey! Wait!
- Jeff!

326
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:41,933
Andrea!

327
00:19:42,067 --> 00:19:44,067
- Wait!
- Jeff!

328
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:46,500
Hazel! Don't hurt Andrea!

329
00:19:46,633 --> 00:19:49,200
Where's my brother?
Bring him out!

330
00:19:49,333 --> 00:19:51,933
I'm suing you for trespassing
and assault!

331
00:19:52,067 --> 00:19:55,333
I'm suing you
for kidnapping and murder!

332
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:58,633
What are you saying?

333
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:00,567
Why are you looking
for Jeffrey here?

334
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,333
Because he's missing.

335
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,567
And there's no one else
who could've had him kidnapped

336
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:05,900
but you.

337
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:07,567
Remember?

338
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:10,100
You told me that
yourself before.

339
00:20:10,233 --> 00:20:11,867
<i> If you really think</i>

340
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:14,567
<i>I had something to do
with Joel's death,</i>

341
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:18,500
<i>aren't you scared I might do
something to you, too?</i>

342
00:20:18,633 --> 00:20:19,600
That?

343
00:20:20,667 --> 00:20:22,033
So what?

344
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,467
You think I'd actually do that?

345
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,500
Just because I said it
doesn't mean I'd do it!

346
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:27,700
I haven't done anything!

347
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,667
Haven't you?

348
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:32,467
Then why is
Jeffrey missing?

349
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:34,000
How would I know?

350
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:37,433
I'm not the lost-and-found
for missing sons and brothers!

351
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,167
Hazel,

352
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:41,767
you're the only one capable
of doing something like this.

353
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,200
Here you go again, Noah.

354
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,633
You, too. Always butting in.

355
00:20:45,767 --> 00:20:48,000
Why should I care where
in the world Jeffrey is?

356
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:52,200
You know, you people really
think highly of me, don't you?

357
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:55,500
Every bad thing that
happens to you, you pin on me?

358
00:20:55,633 --> 00:20:56,633
Yes!

359
00:20:56,933 --> 00:20:58,533
Because you're the only one who
wants to destroy my family!

360
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:02,467
Wow. What is this?
Am I some crime boss now?

361
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:03,867
No,

362
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,000
you're the devil's spawn!

363
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:08,733
- Andrea!
- Andrea!

364
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:11,000
Stop!

365
00:21:11,133 --> 00:21:13,600
Hazel! Don't hurt Andrea!

366
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:15,100
- Hazel!
- Jeff!

367
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:17,700
Where's my brother?

368
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:21,833
Get out!
All of you, get out of here!

369
00:21:22,867 --> 00:21:24,667
And don't ever come back!

370
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,733
Have you no shame,
causing a scene here?

371
00:21:26,867 --> 00:21:28,533
Storming into my house?

372
00:21:28,667 --> 00:21:30,467
Throwing accusations around!

373
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:34,833
Good evening.

374
00:21:34,967 --> 00:21:37,533
We received a report
of trespassing.

375
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:39,200
That was me.

376
00:21:39,533 --> 00:21:40,733
What?

377
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:42,700
You look shocked.

378
00:21:42,867 --> 00:21:45,067
I called them
the moment you showed up.

379
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,000
I knew you'd cause trouble.

380
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:49,133
You think I'd face you
without backup?

381
00:21:49,267 --> 00:21:50,000
What do you think I am?

382
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,233
Get them out of here!

383
00:21:51,367 --> 00:21:52,800
Arrest them,
especially that woman!

384
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:55,300
Take her! She's making a scene!

385
00:21:55,733 --> 00:21:56,833
Look at that! Come on.

386
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:59,033
- Ma'am, let's go.
- You act as if you're so tough.

387
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:00,500
Officers, please
don't hurt her.

388
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:02,167
We'll go. We'll cooperate.

389
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:03,533
Go home!

390
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:05,467
- You monster!
- Let's just go to the station.

391
00:22:08,467 --> 00:22:09,800
Sit!

392
00:22:09,933 --> 00:22:11,300
Sit down!

393
00:22:18,133 --> 00:22:19,300
Eat!

394
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:22,700
Eat!

395
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:26,967
Eat!

396
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,167
Wow!

397
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:29,500
So sweet!

398
00:22:29,633 --> 00:22:31,400
He's feeding him now!

399
00:22:34,533 --> 00:22:36,333
You're going too far!

400
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,367
- If you don't want to eat...
- He needs to eat.

401
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:49,367
So he'll still have strength
for the next round.

402
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:51,467
You animals!

403
00:22:53,433 --> 00:22:54,633
What's this?

404
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:56,167
- He won't eat.
- He won't eat?

405
00:22:58,433 --> 00:22:59,900
Then don't feed him.

406
00:23:00,033 --> 00:23:02,600
Don't even give him water.

407
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:04,367
Go ahead and die there!

408
00:23:04,500 --> 00:23:06,633
Let me out of here, you animals!

409
00:23:06,767 --> 00:23:08,567
Monsters!

410
00:23:14,467 --> 00:23:17,200
Let me out! Help!

411
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:25,433
Jojo, why did you text me?

412
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:28,100
Is what Hazel's saying true?

413
00:23:28,233 --> 00:23:30,000
Do you really want to know?

414
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:32,900
How are you, Jeff?

415
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:36,800
Still holding up?

416
00:23:36,933 --> 00:23:39,533
Let me out of here! Darn you!

417
00:23:39,667 --> 00:23:42,900
Hazel's evil won't win.

418
00:23:43,033 --> 00:23:44,067
But wait.

419
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:46,967
If Hazel kidnapped Jeffrey,

420
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:50,467
how did she know your
brother's flight details?
